8ac52fe7-e9db-48a8-b2f0-7305ab53f4c3">詹姆斯·金奇在《金融时报》上的报道</a>：</p><blockquote><p>中国蓝图的关键是通过创建、扩大和资助一系列中国领导的国家集团，稳步将其对发展中国家的领导地位制度化……这一战略的目标主要有两个：确保世界大部分地区仍然对中国的贸易和投资持开放态度，并利用发展中国家在联合国和其他论坛上的投票权来投射中国的力量和价值观。</p></blockquote><p>其中最重要的集团——或者至少是在西方最受关注和最震惊的集团——是<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BRICS">金砖国家</a>。这个有点奇怪的组织诞生于 22 年前，是高盛分析师吉姆·奥尼尔 (Jim O&#39;Neill) 创建的一项投资策略——基本上是他认为会快速增长的一组大型发展中国家。 “金砖四国”是巴西、俄罗斯、印度、中国等国家名单的缩写。后来，这四个国家实际上聚在一起，决定将高盛的缩写变成一个真正的经济论坛，定期举行会议，讨论如何加快经济发展、创建新的金融机构以及提高发展中国家在全球的整体影响力。世界。 2010年南非加入，金砖四国更名为金砖国家。</p><p>金砖国家不断会晤并提出经济倡议，但均无果而终。我将引用<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/threats-to-the-dollar-are-just-scare">我在二月份写的有关分组的内容</a>：</p><blockquote><p> 2009年，[金砖国家]开始定期举行会议，并试图思考如何建立自己的经济机构——<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/New_Development_Bank">一个与世界银行竞争的新开发银行</a>，一个在货币危机时期相互借钱的<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BRICS_Contingent_Reserve_Arrangement">应急储备安排</a>（类似于IMF 通常会这样做）、<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BRICS_Cable">海底光缆</a>系统等等。</p><p>这最终也没有成功。新开发银行<a href="https://chinadialogue.net/en/business/11661-what-happened-to-brics-bank-s-promise-to-revolutionise-development-finance/">几乎没有发放任何贷款</a>，吉姆·奥尼尔对此表示失望。 2022 年俄罗斯入侵乌克兰时，新开发银行与其断绝了关系。应急储备安排基本上没有起到任何作用，金砖国家电缆也从未发生过。</p></blockquote><p>是的，短短两段文字就足以列出金砖国家组织迄今为止所取得的所有成就的总和。但不知何故，人们仍然相信金砖国家是一个具有全球重要性的组织。我指的不仅仅是西方媒体的人，而是世界上许多国家。最近在南非举行的金砖国家峰会上，该集团<a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-08-24/brics-asks-saudi-iran-4-other-nations-to-join-bloc-to-add-heft?sref=R8NfLgwS">接纳了六个新成员</a>：沙特阿拉伯、伊朗、阿联酋、阿根廷、埃及和埃塞俄比亚。这六个国家是从今年早些时候<a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-04-24/brics-draws-membership-requests-from-19-nations-before-summit?sref=R8NfLgwS">最初提交投标的</a>19 个国家中筛选出来的（尽管有些国家，如<a href="https://en.tempo.co/read/1763880/jokowi-says-indonesia-not-in-a-rush-to-join-brics">印度尼西亚</a>，后来放弃了投标）。目前尚不清楚该组织是否会有两级成员资格，以及一些国家<a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-08-24/brics-summit-2023-south-africa-bloc-invites-saudi-iran-four-others-as-members?sref=R8NfLgwS">是否只是“伙伴”</a> ，但鉴于金砖国家实际上在实际经济政策方面没有<em>采取</em>任何行动，我不确定这是否重要。</p><p>那么，金砖国家为何受到媒体如此广泛的关注呢？原因之一是，有些人认为（有些人<em>希望</em>）这是一个新生的地缘政治甚至军事集团——一个全球反北约，将<a href="https://twitter.com/adam_tooze/status/1695418314690883758">结束美国霸权</a>和西方主导地位等。例如，经济学家布兰科·米拉诺维奇最近写道： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F14c6b4ee-06d1-442d-9623-ccc8bb5076e9_911x376.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F14c6b4ee-06d1-442d-9623-ccc8bb5076e9_911x376.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F14c6b4ee-06d1-442d-9623-ccc8bb5076e9_911x376.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F14c6b4ee-06d1-442d-9623-ccc8bb5076e9_911x376.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F14c6b4ee-06d1-442d-9623-ccc8bb5076e9_911x376.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F14c6b4ee-06d1-442d-9623-ccc8bb5076e9_911x376.jpeg" width="704" height="290.5642151481888" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/14c6b4ee-06d1-442d-9623-ccc8bb5076e9_911x376.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:376,&quot;width&quot;:911,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:704,&quot;bytes&quot;:96544,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F14c6b4ee-06d1-442d-9623-ccc8bb5076e9_911x376.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F14c6b4ee-06d1-442d-9623-ccc8bb5076e9_911x376.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F14c6b4ee-06d1-442d-9623-ccc8bb5076e9_911x376.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F14c6b4ee-06d1-442d-9623-ccc8bb5076e9_911x376.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p>这当然是无稽之谈。中国和俄罗斯确实是针对发达民主国家<a href="https://twitter.com/ProfPaulPoast/status/1642128750509797377">的准联盟</a>，而印度与俄罗斯仍然保持着冷战时期伙伴关系的某种程度的友好关系。但印度和中国是战略竞争对手，而不是盟友。他们偶尔会发生血腥的边境冲突，但时不时地谈论“降级”却<a href="https://twitter.com/tanvi_madan/status/1694013393328345299">未能化解冲突</a>。印度<a href="https://www.reuters.com/world/india/sea-owned-game-free-fire-unavailable-india-after-ban-chinese-apps-2022-02-15/">禁止许多中国应用程序</a>，并开始<a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/india-restricts-laptop-imports-to-boost-local-manufacturing-244cf56a">限制中国商品的进口</a>，尽管它深化了与美国的<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/indiamerica">经济和战略伙伴关系。</a></p><p>印度和中国之间的紧张关系在印度公众舆论中非常明显，与亚洲和其他地区的许多国家一样，印度公众舆论在过去几年中<a href="https://www.pewresearch.org/global/2023/07/27/chinas-approach-to-foreign-policy-gets-largely-negative-reviews-in-24-country-survey/">强烈反对中国</a>。事实上，巴西对中国的好感度也有所下降： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba134564-d200-4f35-849e-f62b91c9746d_995x1028.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba134564-d200-4f35-849e-f62b91c9746d_995x1028.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba134564-d200-4f35-849e-f62b91c9746d_995x1028.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba134564-d200-4f35-849e-f62b91c9746d_995x1028.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba134564-d200-4f35-849e-f62b91c9746d_995x1028.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba134564-d200-4f35-849e-f62b91c9746d_995x1028.jpeg" width="672" height="694.2874371859297" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/ba134564-d200-4f35-849e-f62b91c9746d_995x1028.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1028,&quot;width&quot;:995,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:672,&quot;bytes&quot;:123002,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba134564-d200-4f35-849e-f62b91c9746d_995x1028.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba134564-d200-4f35-849e-f62b91c9746d_995x1028.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba134564-d200-4f35-849e-f62b91c9746d_995x1028.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fba134564-d200-4f35-849e-f62b91c9746d_995x1028.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div><figcaption class="image-caption">资料来源： <a href="https://www.economist.com/international/2023/08/17/the-brics-are-getting-together-in-south-africa">经济学人</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>这是金砖国家不会成为反北约的最明显原因。除此之外还有其他原因——沙特阿拉伯仍然是美国的盟友，巴西、南非、埃塞俄比亚、埃及和阿根廷等国不太愿意卷入大国冲突。俄罗斯和伊朗可能想与中国结盟对抗发达民主国家，但其他国家对此不感兴趣。</p><p>金砖国家在基本价值观上也存在分歧。印度和巴西非常重视民主，而中国、俄罗斯和伊朗则是民主的最大反对者。这就是金砖国家与七国集团之间经常进行比较的诸多原因之一，而七国集团确实<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/G7">提倡</a>一套共同的民主理想。</p><p>这些价值观的差异导致了金砖国家内部的紧张局势。扩大分组的推动力来自中国，而印度和巴西<a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-07-28/india-brazil-push-back-against-china-over-brics-expansion?sref=R8NfLgwS">则试图抵制</a>：</p><blockquote><p><a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/quote/1504Z:IN">印度</a>和<a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/quote/1323Z:BZ">巴西</a>正在抵制中国迅速扩大<a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/quote/BSNT:ES">金砖</a>国家新兴市场集团的努力，以增强其政治影响力并对抗<a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/quote/3352Z:US">美国</a>……中国在这些会议期间多次游说扩大金砖国家的规模……</p><p>两位印度官员表示，在印度反对中国推动扩张之后，金砖国家的入会规则草案就被制定出来了……印度提出了这样的想法：金砖国家如果想加入金砖国家，应该向新兴经济体以及<a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/quote/1310Z:AR">阿根廷</a>和<a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/quote/1119Z:NL">尼日利亚</a>等民主国家寻求帮助。扩大该集团，而不是以其王朝和独裁统治的沙特阿拉伯......</p><p>一名巴西官员表示，巴西正在悄悄努力，以避免金砖国家集团内发生直接对抗，并抵制中国将金砖国家打造成挑战七国集团的对抗性机构的压力。</p></blockquote><p>这使得金砖国家看起来有点像另一个中国领导的组织，人们曾经认为它会成为反北约：<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shanghai_Cooperation_Organisation">上海合作组织</a>，该组织还包括中国、俄罗斯、印度和伊朗，以及沙特阿拉伯和埃及作为“对话伙伴” ”。由于印度和中国之间的紧张关系，该组织最终没有权力、相关性或实际的具体举措。 （事实上​​，如果你仔细观察，你<em>可能会</em>看到印度的一项战略，即加入中国领导的组织，然后抵消其有效性。） 从地缘战略角度来看，金砖国家的结局似乎很可能与上海合作组织的结局完全相同。</p><p>成员国之间的紧张关系也是金砖国家<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/threats-to-the-dollar-are-just-scare">永远不会做俄罗斯提出的事情</a>的原因之一：建立一种共同货币来取代美元。如果印度甚至不让中国应用程序进入该国，它就不可能实现卢比与人民币的统一。鉴于中国相对于其他金砖国家的经济影响力要大得多，参与共同货币计划基本上将消除巴西、印度、沙特阿拉伯、阿根廷、埃及和其他国家的货币政策独立性。俄罗斯和伊朗的经济和金融体系受到严厉制裁，它们可能会看到人民币化的明智之举，但其他国家都不会。坦率地说，金砖国家货币<em>永远不会出现</em>。</p><p>即使没有共同货币，更广泛地取代美国的金融主导地位怎么样？我认为，对于国际金融体系的实际运作方式存在一些常见的误解。国际货币基金组织和世界银行等多边组织向贫穷国家提供贷款，目前这些组织由西方主导。但他们在向贫穷国家提供贷款方面并没有任何接近垄断的行为；中国已经靠自己<a href="https://time.com/6266658/china-emerges-major-global-lender/">做了很多这样的事情</a>。</p><p> So even if the BRICS actually got their Contingent Reserve Arrangement off the ground and turned it into an alternative IMF/World Bank, that would not change the global financial system much from the way it already is. And in practice, the loans made by such a facility would be politically determined in Beijing, and would perform just about as well as China&#39;s, ie <a href="https://apnews.com/article/china-debt-banking-loans-financial-developing-countries-collapse-8df6f9fac3e1e758d0e6d8d5dfbd3ed6">not very well</a> . India and Brazil probably don&#39;t want to get a bunch of poor countries mad at them for engaging in “debt trap diplomacy”, so I predict they&#39;ll push to limit IMF-like or World Bank-like lending by the BRICS.</p><p> Other than the dollar&#39;s role as a reserve/payment currency and the existence of multilateral lending institutions, there&#39;s just not that much to the international financial system. The only other big piece is global payment infrastructure, like SWIFT. The US and Europe did show that they could throw their weight around by limiting access to this infrastructure when they put financial sanctions on Russia following the invasion of Ukraine. But the effect of those financial sanctions <a href="https://theovershoot.co/p/back-to-square-one-on-the-russia">lasted only about a year</a> , as Russia eventually found other ways to pay and get paid. And that was about the most fearsome financial weapon in the West&#39;s arsenal.</p><p> So there&#39;s really not much to the supposed Western or US control of the global financial system — meaning there&#39;s just not much for BRICS to replace in the first place. The outsized role the US plays in the system exists primarily because of convenience, not hegemony; to see this, witness how the BRICS&#39; New Development Bank <a href="https://www.wsj.com/articles/a-bank-china-backed-to-challenge-the-dollar-now-needs-the-dollar-d9dc27ee">does most of its borrowing in dollars</a> . It&#39;s not because the US makes them do it; it&#39;s just easier.</p><p> The Western press&#39; final worry about the BRICS is that the bloc will cement Chinese economic and leadership over the developing world. Here&#39;s Kynge:</p><blockquote><p> The crucial context to this strategy is that by seeking increased leadership over the global south, China is throwing in its lot with the largest and fastest-growing part of the world…<br><br> “China will always be a member of the family of developing countries,” Xi told a forum in 2021. “We will continue to do our utmost in raising the representation and voice of developing nations in the global governance system.”</p></blockquote><p> This is certainly something that China&#39;s leaders have in mind: </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F35e064c4-c471-41dd-bc3c-3c56a6186210_801x786.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F35e064c4-c471-41dd-bc3c-3c56a6186210_801x786.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F35e064c4-c471-41dd-bc3c-3c56a6186210_801x786.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F35e064c4-c471-41dd-bc3c-3c56a6186210_801x786.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F35e064c4-c471-41dd-bc3c-3c56a6186210_801x786.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F35e064c4-c471-41dd-bc3c-3c56a6186210_801x786.jpeg" width="610" height="598.5767790262172" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/35e064c4-c471-41dd-bc3c-3c56a6186210_801x786.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:786,&quot;width&quot;:801,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:610,&quot;bytes&quot;:110962,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F35e064c4-c471-41dd-bc3c-3c56a6186210_801x786.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F35e064c4-c471-41dd-bc3c-3c56a6186210_801x786.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F35e064c4-c471-41dd-bc3c-3c56a6186210_801x786.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F35e064c4-c471-41dd-bc3c-3c56a6186210_801x786.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p> Now, if I were China&#39;s Ministry of Foreign Affairs, I wouldn&#39;t go around proudly declaring that my country will never reach developed status — no one thinks the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Middle_income_trap">middle-income trap</a> is a cool place to be. But in any case, it&#39;s clear that China thinks that in light of their deteriorating image and stagnating exports in developed nations, they can pivot to being the leader of a developing-world economic bloc.</p><p> But if you look at the BRICS countries, including the new entrants, you&#39;ll see that very few of them are actually developing rapidly. They&#39;re mostly natural resource exporters, whose economies have plateaued at varying levels of income. Other than China itself, only India and Ethiopia have actually grown by a significant amount over the last decade or so. </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3c05a9ba-a379-492f-aa39-af1d01bbfb03_1020x836.png" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3c05a9ba-a379-492f-aa39-af1d01bbfb03_1020x836.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3c05a9ba-a379-492f-aa39-af1d01bbfb03_1020x836.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3c05a9ba-a379-492f-aa39-af1d01bbfb03_1020x836.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3c05a9ba-a379-492f-aa39-af1d01bbfb03_1020x836.png 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3c05a9ba-a379-492f-aa39-af1d01bbfb03_1020x836.png" width="1020" height="836" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/3c05a9ba-a379-492f-aa39-af1d01bbfb03_1020x836.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:836,&quot;width&quot;:1020,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:228673,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3c05a9ba-a379-492f-aa39-af1d01bbfb03_1020x836.png 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3c05a9ba-a379-492f-aa39-af1d01bbfb03_1020x836.png 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3c05a9ba-a379-492f-aa39-af1d01bbfb03_1020x836.png 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F3c05a9ba-a379-492f-aa39-af1d01bbfb03_1020x836.png 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div class="image-link-expand"><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#FFFFFF" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="lucide lucide-maximize2"><polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p> I&#39;ve already mentioned India&#39;s economic rivalry with China, so in terms of rapid growth potential in the BRICS that China could tap into, that really only leaves Ethiopia, which is riven by deep political instability that sometimes <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tigray_War">spills into civil war</a> .</p><p> The bulk of the growth potential of the world right now lies in the countries of South and Southeast Asia — India, Bangladesh, Indonesia, Philippines, Vietnam, and so on. But except for India, they&#39;re not in BRICS. And most of these countries&#39; <a href="https://www.csis.org/analysis/assessing-us-and-chinese-influence-southeast-asia">opinions</a> of <a href="https://www.pewresearch.org/global/2023/07/27/chinas-approach-to-foreign-policy-gets-largely-negative-reviews-in-24-country-survey/">China</a> range from mildly unfriendly to openly hostile. As China&#39;s territorial and hegemonic ambitions in Asia grow, these countries are drawing closer to India, Japan, the US, Europe, and each other. Some will still welcome Chinese investment and goods, but they&#39;ll try to balance that out with investment and trade linkages with China&#39;s democratic rivals as well. And China&#39;s economic slowdown is likely to reduce much of its mindshare in developing nations, as is <a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-08-25/china-s-slowdown-casts-a-shadow-on-lula-s-big-bet-on-beijing?sref=R8NfLgwS">already happening in Brazil</a> .</p><p> So anyway, every aspect of the threat that some in the Western press perceive from BRICS is essentially fake. More <a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2023-08-25/brics-shows-it-s-little-more-than-a-meaningless-acronym?sref=R8NfLgwS">incisive</a> <a href="https://www.bloomberg.com/opinion/articles/2023-08-21/the-brics-are-not-the-anti-west-and-not-even-a-bloc?sref=R8NfLgwS">commentators</a> see that the organization is likely to become something like the SCO — an acronym looking for a purpose, coupled with a vague notion of geo-economic power that never quite coalesces into anything real. </p><div><hr></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?"><span>现在订阅</span></a></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/brics-is-fake?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"> <a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/brics-is-fake?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share"><span>分享</span></a></p>; 
